        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Shouhou">Shouhou</a
      >, etc.)
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <b>Preloaders / Fast-Loaders</b> (ex.
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Richelieu">Richelieu</a
      >,
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Aquila">Aquila</a
      >,
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Independence"
        >Independence (Retrofit)</a
      >,
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Vittorio_Veneto"
        >Vittorio Veneto</a
      >, etc.)
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <b>Self-Heals</b> (ex.
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Neptune">Neptune</a
      >,
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Minneapolis">Minneapolis</a
      >,
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Phoenix">Phoenix (Retrofit)</a
      >, etc.)
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <i
    >Note: Some ships (ex. Unicorn) fall into multiple categories. READ SKILLS
    FOR MORE INFORMATION!</i
  >
</p>
<p>Remember:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      <b
        >Do NOT choose ships for farming fleets based off of ONLY these
        qualities.</b
      >
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          These ships <i>help</i>; they are not mandatory for efficient farming.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <b
        >Do NOT use oil cost as a consideration when determining what ships to
        use.</b
      >
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          Investing in ships that have a purpose for future content, whether
          that be through leveling them or through their fleet technology
          bonuses, is better in the long run.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<br />

